headline: Assessing Procter & Gamble (PG) Valuation After Earnings Beat And Tide Evo Launch
summary: Procter & Gamble (PG) is back in focus after topping fiscal second quarter earnings expectations, drawing analyst upgrades and renewed attention to its mix of new products, including the nationwide launch of Tide evo. See our latest analysis for Procter & Gamble. Those product launches and the earnings beat have coincided with a clear shift in sentiment, with the share price at US$165.17 and a 30 day share price return of 10% feeding into a 5 year total shareholder return of 50.76%.
